3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
4 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. As used in this section:
8 1. “Antisemitism” has the same meaning as provided for by the
9 International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance Working Definition of
10 Antisemitism, including its contemporary examples, as it was adopted
11 on May 26, 2016;
12 2. “Institution of higher education” means an institution of
13 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
14 Education; and
15 3. “Public school” shall have the same meaning as provided for
16 in Section 1-106 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
17 B. Discrimination on the basis of race, ethnicity, national
18 origin, sex, disability, religion, or marital status against a
19 student or an employee in an institution of higher education or a
20 public school in this state shall be prohibited. No person in this
21 state shall, on the basis of race, ethnicity, national origin, sex,
22 disability, religion, or marital status, be excluded from
23 participating in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to
24 discrimination under any institution of higher education or public
